definition: to insert/stick in/pierce/to take part in/to interfere/to interpose
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: The F14 offers compact package dimensions and a pluggable pin header.
sentences.chinese: 在女性14例提供了紧凑的封装尺寸和可插入针。

sentences.english: It works better if the blade's back edge (spine) somewhat touches the inner back edge of the scabbard while drawing out (same while inserting in).
sentences.chinese: 如果刀背略微贴着刀削的背部拔出会更好，插入亦然。

sentences.english: A column break inserted in the last column of a page will act as a page break.
sentences.chinese: 插入到页面最后一列的分栏符会成为分页符。

sentences.english: He inserted a slip marking his place in the book.
sentences.chinese: 他在书中插入纸页，以标明他读到的地方。

sentences.english: Whether it is a prototype, slide, insert or unscrewing, we have the experience to produce it.
sentences.chinese: 无论是样机，幻灯片，插入或挂画，我们有经验产生。

sentences.english: If you choose to validate documents, you typically validate at insert time.
sentences.chinese: 如果选择验证文档，那么通常是在插入时进行验证。

sentences.english: Knock this stick into the deep hole, please.
sentences.chinese: 请把这根枝棍插入这个深洞里。

sentences.english: He often parenthesizes a talk with jokes.
sentences.chinese: 他常常在交谈中插入几句玩笑话。

sentences.english: His clinical condition improved after the insertion of an intercostal chest tube.
sentences.chinese: 病患之病况在插入胸管治疗后立即稳定下来。

sentences.english: That number actually refers to the number of lines inserted.
sentences.chinese: 这个数字实际上指的是插入的行的数量。

sentences.english: Mary duplicated her mother's way of standing with her hands in her pockets.
sentences.chinese: 玛丽模仿她母亲两手插入口袋站立的样子。

sentences.english: My assistants were hanging over the edge of the pool with plugged-in strobes .
sentences.chinese: 我的助手们拿着插入式电源闸挤在游泳池边上。

sentences.english: However Cuzco inserted mercilessly and the uterine ostium is exposed.
sentences.chinese: 然而无情和库斯科插入子宫口暴露。

sentences.english: If cabling is correct, power off the device and reseat the interface card.
sentences.chinese: 假如缆线连接是正确的，关掉设备且重新插入介面卡。

sentences.english: First, a suction tube with a knife-like edge is inserted into the womb.
sentences.chinese: 首先，吸力管刀一样的优势是插入到子宫。

definition: to insert/to stick in/to plug in (an electronic device)
to eject/to exit from/to pop up
to take out/to extract/to draw out
to break/to sever/to turn off (electric switch)
to aim at/to target/to point at/to be directed at/registration/alignment (mechanical engineering)
